# UI errors and warnings — people-friendly copy

All messages shown to users (inline errors, toasts, alerts) must be understandable without technical background.

## Rules

- Map API/network failures through `toUserMessage()` in `apps/web/src/lib/user-messages.ts`
- Do not show: HTTP status codes, stack traces, raw JSON, Prisma/Redis errors, env names, or CLI hints
- Log technical details with `console.error` in development only
- Keep messages to one short sentence when possible

## Examples

**Bad**
```tsx
setErr("Internal Server Error");
setErr("API connect failed — run `pnpm dev`, API :4000");
setErr(JSON.stringify(err));
```

**Good**
```tsx
setErr(toUserMessage(e, "auth"));
// "Something went wrong on our side. Please try again in a moment."
// "We couldn't reach the server. Check your connection and try again."
```

**Bad**
```tsx
{err && <p>{res.status} {await res.text()}</p>}
```

**Good**
```tsx
{err && <p className="text-sm text-red-600" role="alert">{err}</p>}
```
